<para>Send a hardware input event over CAN to the master node. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Packs controlId and value into an 8-byte CAN frame on CAN_ID_EVT_n (where n = <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup_1aecfca5a88d5758bb09efa658a633d0c6" kindref="member">nodeId()</ref>). Intended to be called by InputBase subclasses.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>controlId</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Identifies the physical control (HID range 0x0010–0x00FF, or DCS-BIOS address 0x8000+). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>value</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Current control value (0/1 for switches, 0–65535 for axes). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>true on successful TX, false if the CAN mailbox was full. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
